Vice President Kamala Harris hosted Guatemalan President Alejandro Giammattei for a virtual bilateral meeting to discuss addressing immediate relief needs of the Guatemalan people and cooperation on migration. They announced an additional $310 million in U.S. government support for humanitarian relief and food insecurity. Both leaders committed to managing migration in an orderly and humane manner, with Guatemala increasing border security personnel and safeguards. They also agreed to strengthen law enforcement cooperation to combat criminal activities and establish orderly and legal channels for migrants. Migrant Resource Centers will be opened in Guatemala to provide services for migrants seeking lawful pathways and protection. Lastly, the importance of creating economic opportunities and addressing corruption was emphasized to attract investment and improve conditions for the people of Guatemala.